text: Tate is an American western series that aired from 8 June to 14 September, 1960 on NBC for 13 episodes and one season. It starred Daniel McLean and was created by Harry Julian Fink of Dirty Harry fame. ==Other websites== * *Tate opening credits on YouTube Category:Western (genre) television series Category:NBC network series Category:1960s television series Category:1960 television series debuts Category:1960 television series endings Category:English-language television programs
